there are 4 methods to find date by js.

.........................................................
let a= new Date();
console.log(a);

// output:     2021-05-18T06:19:09.916Z
.........................................................
let a= new Date().toLocaleString();
console.log(a);
// output:     5/18/2021, 11:31:25 AM
.........................................................
let a= new Date().toString();
console.log(a);

// output:     Tue May 18 2021 11:32:21 
                GMT+0500 (Pakistan Standard Time)

....................Date.now() .....................................
Date.now():
 
            returns miliseconds from january 1,1970
Example:
                 let a= Date.now();
           console.log(new Date(a).toLocaleString());            
